This is the kind of stuff in Angular/Javascript that is nuts:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
sampleApp.config([&#039;$routeProvider&#039;, function (routeProvider) {&lt;br /&gt;
    ...&lt;br /&gt;
);&lt;br /&gt;
}]);&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
So the config method takes in an array of strings and functions? This is a cognitive debt for the developer. There is nothing intuitive about it. There is a difference between a framework that works for you (e.g. Spring) and a framework that you work for (Angular!). &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
As Angular matures, in a few years, you will look at this code and be dumbfounded.
